text:
This C program defines a function named `write_footer` that takes a file pointer as an argument. The function first checks if the global variable `opt_xml` is true. If it is, then the function writes `</mysqldump>
` to the specified file and checks for any I/O errors.If `opt_xml` is false and `opt_compact` is also false, the function performs the following operations:- If the global variable `opt_tz_utc` is true, it prints `/*!40103 SET TIME_ZONE=@OLD_TIME_ZONE */;
` to the file.- It then prints:  - `/*!40101 SET SQL_MODE=@OLD_SQL_MODE */;
`  - `/*!40101 SET CHARACTER_SET_CLIENT=@OLD_CHARACTER_SET_CLIENT */;
`  - `/*!40101 SET CHARACTER_SET_RESULTS=@OLD_CHARACTER_SET_RESULTS */;
`  - `/*!40101 SET COLLATION_CONNECTION=@OLD_COLLATION_CONNECTION */;
`  - `/*!40111 SET SQL_NOTES=@OLD_SQL_NOTES */;
`  - Two newline characters ("
") are also printed.Furthermore, if a specific condition is met (e.g., `opt_dump_date` being true), the function generates a timestamp string using `get_date` function and appends a comment line to the file indicating the dump completion date/time.Finally, the function checks for any I/O errors after performing the necessary operations on the file.
